All instructional learning model selection forms are due tomorrow, July 30, for returning Andrews ISD students. Parents can login to their Skyward Family Access to access the form.

If you have already made your selection and wish to make a change, you may do so by following these steps:

post_text:
PARENTS & ATHLETES:
Summer workouts will begin on Monday, June 8th. With the challenges of COVID-19, there are many guidelines we will have to place on the weight room workouts for the safety and health of all student-athletes and coaching staff.

1. Only 18 athletes are allowed in the weight room at a time
2. By signing in and entering the weight room, each coach & athlete are affirming that they have answered no to each question.
3. Athletes will enter the weight room from the North entrance and exit from the South entrance.
4. Equipment will be wiped down and disinfected after every use by the athletes.
5. Athletes may not group up and must keep the 6-foot spacing requirements. However, a spotter is allowed for lifts.
6. This is only for the use of CURRENT student-athletes (incoming 7th-12th grade).

Individual sport head coaches will reach out to their teams to insure each student-athlete understands their weight room time blocks and the guidelines we must adhere to. Please check the list below for your sport-specific workout time.

2. By signing in and entering the weight room, each coach & athlete are affirming that they have answered no to each question.

post_text:
PARENTS & STUDENT-ATHLETES:
With the reopening of the weight room and summer workouts starting up for the summer next week, we want to make sure we are doing our best to stay in accordance with the guidelines provided by the UIL.

Please work with our coaching staff as we venture into this uncharted territory.

We will have specific times for student-athletes to come and workout. Only a limited a number of student-athletes will be allowed at a time. This is open to CURRENT student-athletes only.

Our coaching staff will be on hand to wipe down equipment down between use of each student-athlete. There will be hand sanitizing stations around the weight room for the student-athletes use.

If you answered yes to any of these questions on any day, PLEASE do not attend any workouts or sport-specific workouts until your symptoms are gone for the health and safety of our staff and the other student-athletes.

Last night, 4th grader Tytan Richters was surprised with his make-a-wish destination.

Tytan was diagnosed with Juvenile Dermatomyositis, JDM, in May of 2017. JDM is an auto-immune disease that attacks muscles and soft tissue instead of protecting them.

Though it’s been a long time coming, Tytan and his family learned they will make a trip to Tahiti for his Make-a-Wish reveal.
